WEBVTT

00:02.275 --> 00:05.609
We are celebrating the union
of Zorn, Defender of Zephyria,

00:05.644 --> 00:07.978
Conqueror of the Tribes of Agon,

00:08.013 --> 00:10.147
Decapitator of the
Dark Herdsmen of Grith,

00:10.182 --> 00:13.016
to Edie...
Bennett.

00:13.052 --> 00:16.720
So, by the power bestowed
by the god of war,

00:16.755 --> 00:19.322
- I pronounce...
- I oppose this union.

00:23.462 --> 00:28.265
- Sir Pent.
- You can't marry... a dead woman.

00:30.236 --> 00:32.069
_

00:35.130 --> 00:38.053
I'm sorry, honey. I know I
promised not to disembowel

00:38.054 --> 00:40.777
anyone at our wedding, but he
was about to explode your head.

00:40.813 --> 00:42.813
<i>I love you, babe.</i>

00:42.848 --> 00:45.415
See?
I'm glad we watched that.

00:45.451 --> 00:46.583
That's exactly how I want
my hair for our ceremony.

00:46.619 --> 00:48.719
So, we're not
gonna talk about how Zorn

00:48.754 --> 00:50.854
just saved you from a
murderous snake person

00:50.890 --> 00:51.989
at your own wedding?

00:52.024 --> 00:55.192
Oh, he was just an ex.
We went on, like, three dates.

00:55.227 --> 00:57.327
Four if you count
the initial kidnapping.

00:57.363 --> 01:01.098
You know, I've never seen
you look at me that way.

01:01.133 --> 01:03.000
Would you call this
a French braid?

01:03.035 --> 01:04.768
- No, that's a Dutch braid.
- Hmm.

01:04.803 --> 01:07.738
I'd like to see Zorn
correctly identify a braid.

01:07.773 --> 01:09.340
<i>I love you, Edie, and,</i>

01:09.341 --> 01:12.455
<i>- hey, I love your Dutch braid.
- Son of a...</i>

01:17.656 --> 01:20.223
<i><font color="cyan"> sync & correction by f1nc0
~ Addic7ed.com ~ </font></i>

01:20.486 --> 01:23.420
- Hey, Alan.
- Oh, hey, Layla. What's up?

01:23.455 --> 01:25.589
I'm plant sitting for my aunt.
She's away this week,

01:25.624 --> 01:28.058
and I was just wondering
if maybe you wanted

01:28.093 --> 01:30.260
to come over tomorrow
and hang out.

01:30.296 --> 01:32.563
Totally, yeah.
Plants and no aunts?

01:32.598 --> 01:34.398
That sounds like my kind
of a party.

01:34.433 --> 01:36.066
Cool. Well, I'll text you
the address.

01:36.101 --> 01:38.201
Cool.

01:38.237 --> 01:40.804
Oh, uh, by the way,
it's-it's a beach house, so...

01:40.839 --> 01:43.507
- bring your swimsuit.
- Beach house?

01:43.542 --> 01:46.610
- See you later.
- Yup.

01:52.027 --> 01:54.661
<i>Wait, isn't Dr. Klorpins in Zephyria?</i>

01:54.697 --> 01:56.897
Yeah, well, that's what he wants
the FBI to think, too...

01:56.932 --> 01:59.966
and the CIA...
and Mothers Against Drunk Driving.

02:00.002 --> 02:02.235
Zorn.
You're looking well.

02:02.271 --> 02:04.337
Someone must be taking
his fish person oil.

02:04.373 --> 02:07.941
Keeps the muscles tight
and the mind focused on eggs.

02:07.976 --> 02:09.675
That is actually why I'm here.

02:09.711 --> 02:11.478
Well, there's a fish guy
in room two.

02:11.513 --> 02:14.948
- Go on. Take a suck on his oil hole.
- All right.

02:14.983 --> 02:17.617
And this time maybe I'll let
the fish guy return the favor.

02:22.424 --> 02:25.726
Uh, hey, Dr. Klorpins,
what-what is, uh, Zephyritol?

02:25.761 --> 02:28.662
Oh, it's just a drug
that changes Zephyrian bodies

02:28.697 --> 02:30.831
so that they look
like regular bodies.

02:30.866 --> 02:32.132
And that really works?

02:32.167 --> 02:33.934
Like on any body part?
I don't know,

02:33.969 --> 02:35.802
just like a random example,
what about legs?

02:35.838 --> 02:39.840
Well, does Blake Lively look like
she has tentacles under her skirt?

02:39.875 --> 02:42.075
Then I guess it works.

02:42.111 --> 02:44.010
Hey, uh, do you think
I could have some?

02:44.046 --> 02:46.847
Sure, I got some free samples
here somewhere.

02:46.882 --> 02:49.750
Let's see, scalpel...
oh, pus kit... ow!

02:49.785 --> 02:53.653
There's got to be a better place
to store old, dirty needles.

02:53.689 --> 02:55.021
Here you go, squirt.

02:56.125 --> 02:58.592
Ooh, all right, well, just give
me my flu shot and a lollipop,

02:58.627 --> 02:59.960
and let's get
the hell out of here.

03:07.136 --> 03:09.035
Craig. Did you hear that?

03:09.071 --> 03:11.938
Does this look like the face
of someone who didn't hear that?

03:11.974 --> 03:13.073
You want to go check it out?

03:13.108 --> 03:15.375
Does this feel like
the heartbeat of someone

03:15.410 --> 03:17.244
who wants to go
check something out?

03:17.279 --> 03:18.678
Oh.

03:18.714 --> 03:20.313
Okay, we've got to do something.

03:20.349 --> 03:22.415
Okay, um,
let's just stay in bed,

03:22.451 --> 03:24.985
and if the murderer comes
in here, then I'll-I'll, like,

03:25.020 --> 03:26.686
distract him with a cloud
of feathers,

03:26.722 --> 03:29.656
and you make a run for it.

03:31.760 --> 03:32.726
What are you doing?

03:32.761 --> 03:35.962
- Nothing. I just texted Zorn.
- Okay, well, fine.

03:35.998 --> 03:38.131
We'll just call Zorn,
let him swoop in,

03:38.167 --> 03:40.000
and I'll just sit here
and be useless.

03:40.035 --> 03:41.067
Ooh.

03:41.103 --> 03:43.704
Well, looks like it was
a branch hitting your window.

03:43.705 --> 03:46.673
Don't worry, though.
I hacked it off, uprooted the tree,

03:46.708 --> 03:48.842
and salted the earth so nothing
can ever grow there again.

03:48.877 --> 03:50.677
Oh, I can break a stick, Edie.

03:50.712 --> 03:52.312
If I had known
that was the problem,

03:52.347 --> 03:54.114
I would've taken
care of it myself.

03:54.149 --> 03:55.849
Oh, I know you would've, sweetie.

03:55.884 --> 03:58.766
Hey, just so you
know, Craig, she's lying.

03:58.801 --> 04:02.622
Yeah, well, just so you know,
Zorn, you could be mean.

04:08.897 --> 04:10.530
I hate to sound
like such a dreamer,

04:10.566 --> 04:12.465
but there's got to be a
better way to shred documents.

04:12.501 --> 04:16.236
Actually, the machine you use
to make your smoothies

04:16.271 --> 04:19.673
- is technically a paper...
- Todd! No one likes a know-it-all.

04:20.642 --> 04:23.844
Zorn. Hey, hey,
didn't you get my memo?

04:23.879 --> 04:28.849
Hey, Blake Erickson,
the CEO of Sanitation Solutions,

04:28.884 --> 04:31.084
is coming in from Houston
to visit our branch.

04:31.119 --> 04:33.353
So I need everyone,
especially you,

04:33.388 --> 04:35.055
to be on their best behavior.

04:35.090 --> 04:36.756
That means no blasting
Blues Traveler

04:36.792 --> 04:38.458
"'cause it's 'Run-Around'
time somewhere."

04:38.493 --> 04:41.561
Geez, relax, man. You're
the most badass boss I know.

04:41.597 --> 04:43.096
Why are you so worried
about this guy?

04:43.131 --> 04:46.299
'Cause I think Erickson hates me.
Last time he was here,

04:46.335 --> 04:49.086
I said I'd rather be
dead in a ditch than alive

04:49.087 --> 04:51.838
watching a tennis match. Turns
out he's a huge tennis fan

04:51.874 --> 04:53.907
and his wife was found
dead in a ditch.

04:53.942 --> 04:56.877
Personally, I'd rather be dead
in a ditch than at a tennis match.

04:56.912 --> 04:59.346
I agree, but please
don't say that

04:59.381 --> 05:01.314
in front of our CEO when he
gets here.

05:01.350 --> 05:03.416
Okay, well, shut up a second.
Zorn on the horn.

05:03.452 --> 05:06.553
Well, well, well.
No, I'd-I'd love to help you out,

05:06.588 --> 05:08.955
but I'm super busy
here at work, okay? Whoops.

05:08.991 --> 05:13.193
No, he's not!
Whoever this is, he'll be right there!

05:13.228 --> 05:15.662
Hey, sorry it took me so long.
Traffic on the freeway

05:15.697 --> 05:18.632
was terribly hard to walk
through on foot.

05:18.667 --> 05:22.569
Zorn, I want you to train me
to be more like you.

05:22.604 --> 05:25.698
Really? You need me
to train you to hate... you?

05:25.733 --> 05:28.842
No, I want you to train me
to be a warrior.

05:28.877 --> 05:31.745
If I'm gonna marry Edie,
I need to be able to protect her.

05:31.780 --> 05:33.914
Being sweet, lovable Craig
isn't enough.

05:33.949 --> 05:35.882
I need to be tough,
lovable Craig.

05:35.918 --> 05:39.286
She already has that man: Alangulon.
The fruit of my loins!

05:39.321 --> 05:41.688
Zorn, I want you to picture Alan

05:41.723 --> 05:44.324
trying to stand up
to a meth-crazed mugger.

05:44.359 --> 05:46.960
All right, cool. I'll dust
off the old imagination here,

05:46.995 --> 05:48.128
let me see what I got.

05:48.163 --> 05:51.564
Oh, my God! That junkie
tore him to bits in seconds.

05:51.600 --> 05:54.434
I mean, that was like running
a tomato through a band saw.

05:54.469 --> 05:57.103
Why-Why did you make
me picture that?

05:57.139 --> 05:59.539
- So you see my point, Zorn.
- Fine.

05:59.574 --> 06:04.010
I, Zorn, will make it
my mission to train thee,

06:04.046 --> 06:07.647
Craig,
in the ways of the warrior!

06:07.683 --> 06:09.416
Here you go, kale salad,

06:09.451 --> 06:11.518
- no Parmesan, extra lemon juice.
- Ooh.

06:11.553 --> 06:13.320
B.S.! He'll have a live pig,

06:13.355 --> 06:16.489
