Wait a second.

06:49.891 --> 06:52.451
Only one...

06:54.717 --> 06:55.716
- So, this is the place.
- Whoa.

06:55.751 --> 06:58.469
Uh, my aunt can't get
pregnant and, uh, she doesn't

06:58.470 --> 07:01.188
trust animals, so she says
her plants are her children.

07:01.224 --> 07:02.656
Wow.

07:02.692 --> 07:05.059
- Oh, you got aloe!
- Yeah, we got aloe,

07:05.094 --> 07:06.961
we got drinks,
we got everything.

07:06.996 --> 07:08.662
Aloe is the best.
Aloe vera.

07:08.698 --> 07:10.297
You know, a lot of people
say that aloe should not

07:10.333 --> 07:12.366
be applied to exquisite and
elegant legs such as these.

07:12.401 --> 07:13.434
Really?

07:13.469 --> 07:14.735
You mind if I, uh,
crack one of these off?

07:14.770 --> 07:16.070
Hop to it.

07:16.105 --> 07:17.538
Only the best
for the best legs.

07:17.573 --> 07:19.874
How often do you apply?

07:19.909 --> 07:23.043
Every day at breakfast I apply
aloe to my real, human legs.

07:23.079 --> 07:25.146
You really do have amazing,
amazing legs.

07:25.181 --> 07:27.615
Oh, you know what?
Speaking of...

07:27.650 --> 07:29.183
these legs aren't
gonna tone themselves.

07:29.218 --> 07:30.651
Mind if I hop on this?

07:30.686 --> 07:31.685
Not at all.

07:31.721 --> 07:35.289
Wow, you know your plants
and you can climb stairs.

07:35.324 --> 07:37.591
- Oh, my God!
- Oh, yup, I'm good.

07:37.627 --> 07:39.293
Just a little
too much aloe on there.

07:40.396 --> 07:42.263
Zorn, is this
really necessary?

07:42.298 --> 07:43.864
All right, the first step
in being a warrior

07:43.900 --> 07:45.099
is looking like a warrior.

07:45.134 --> 07:48.602
Hey, you look, like,
so fierce, man.

07:48.638 --> 07:51.138
Look at that.
I mean, you are no longer

07:51.174 --> 07:52.540
Craig the Therapist.
You're more like

07:52.575 --> 07:54.842
Craig the Psycho-Therapist.

07:54.877 --> 07:56.277
But did you have
to rip the sleeves off?

07:56.312 --> 07:58.112
I just bought this shirt
last week.

07:58.147 --> 08:01.282
Warriors don't have sleeves.
We need our arms free,

08:01.317 --> 08:02.816
you know, for
windmill punches

08:02.852 --> 08:04.885
and raising our fists
victoriously, like this.

08:04.921 --> 08:07.821
Yeah!
Ha-ha.

08:07.857 --> 08:11.113
By the power of
Fullerton University Online,

08:11.148 --> 08:13.093
Continuing Adult Education Division,

08:13.129 --> 08:15.496
<i>Department of Psychology
and Music.</i>

08:15.531 --> 08:17.731
<i>You shall not pass!</i>

08:28.010 --> 08:30.711
Zorn.

08:52.401 --> 08:54.201
Yes.

08:55.371 --> 08:57.789
You know, I
totally thought you didn't

08:57.790 --> 09:00.207
know how to swim, but
you're actually pretty good.

09:00.243 --> 09:02.376
Well, I take a bath
every Sunday,

09:02.411 --> 09:06.113
so what is that but a tiny ocean?

09:08.851 --> 09:10.317
Yeah, you should
come back Saturday.

09:10.353 --> 09:12.086
I'm gonna be here
all day, so...

09:12.121 --> 09:17.858
- Oh, uh, that sounds good.
- It's cold.

09:17.893 --> 09:19.893
Oh, you want to, uh,
wear this towel?

09:19.929 --> 09:22.062
Thank you.

09:22.098 --> 09:25.065
Uh... hold on a second.
Let me take that.

09:25.101 --> 09:26.767
- Uh...
- What?

09:26.802 --> 09:29.069
I just, uh, I just caught a...
caught a spider, yeah,

09:29.105 --> 09:32.706
between my leg and the towel.
I got to go take care of that.

09:42.171 --> 09:44.271
Oh, Alan,
how was the beach house?

09:44.306 --> 09:45.739
A super magical day.

09:45.775 --> 09:47.775
I don't want to talk about it,
though. Thanks.

09:47.810 --> 09:52.246
Well, if you decide you do want to
talk about it, I'm here.

09:52.281 --> 09:53.881
Come on, honey.
Let's rap.

09:53.916 --> 09:56.917
- Kid's still say that, right?
- No, we don't, no.

09:56.952 --> 09:58.919
Well, do you want half
of my sandwich?

09:58.954 --> 10:00.621
<i>No, ok... fine,
sure, don't come in.</i>

10:00.656 --> 10:03.112
<i>Just shove it
under the door, okay? Bye.</i>

10:04.326 --> 10:05.959
<i>These numbers are terrible, Linda.</i>

10:05.995 --> 10:08.128
I know. We've been
having some...

10:08.164 --> 10:10.197
employee productivity issues.

10:10.232 --> 10:12.699
Todd!
Where have you been?

10:12.735 --> 10:14.568
I need that report on my
desk by the end of the day.

10:14.603 --> 10:17.037
Oh, I'm sorry.
I was just playing some tennis.

10:17.072 --> 10:18.338
It helps me concentrate.

10:18.374 --> 10:21.208
- I'm gonna tackle the report right now.
- Tennis, you say?

10:21.243 --> 10:24.778
Oh.
Important client.

10:24.814 --> 10:29.183
I'll be right back.
Hey, Edie, What's up?

10:29.218 --> 10:31.118
- Hey, have you seen Zorn?
- No.

10:31.153 --> 10:32.152
Why? Everything okay?

10:32.188 --> 10:33.654
Well, I'm worried about Alan.

10:33.689 --> 10:35.422
He had a 40-minute shower cry.

10:35.458 --> 10:36.757
I don't know much
about parenting.

10:36.792 --> 10:39.626
I'm gonna guess gay.
Okay, got to go.

10:39.662 --> 10:42.563
What do you think we can do
about our productivity problem?

10:42.598 --> 10:44.698
Well, I do have some
ideas, actually...

10:44.733 --> 10:47.400
Todd calls his mom
on company time.

10:48.417 --> 10:51.018
<i>Okay, warrior,
let's build up that confidence.</i>

10:51.053 --> 10:53.187
I'm gonna do a power poem.

10:53.222 --> 10:55.723
Capable.

10:55.758 --> 10:58.325
Resourceful.
Acrobatic.

10:58.361 --> 11:00.260
Incorrigible.

11:00.296 --> 11:02.629
Giggly?
Sometimes, yeah.

11:04.400 --> 11:05.366
Craig!

11:05.401 --> 11:08.569
Oh. Zorn.
Do not barge into my bathroom.

11:08.604 --> 11:11.338
Or my bedroom.
Or my dreams.

11:11.374 --> 11:13.240
All right, Craig, you
can become a warrior,

11:13.275 --> 11:15.476
or you can become someone
whose privacy I respect,

11:15.511 --> 11:16.977
but you can't become both.

11:17.012 --> 11:19.880
Zorn, do not slap me again.
Enough is enough.

11:21.504 --> 11:24.605
You stood up to me.
You are now a warrior.

11:24.640 --> 11:26.006
What about learning how
to fight?

11:26.041 --> 11:28.041
Nah, you're never gonna
be good at that, no.

11:28.077 --> 11:29.877
Here's a little tip, though,
just sucker punch people.

11:29.912 --> 11:31.311
Now get dressed
and drive me to work.

11:31.347 --> 11:33.480
- Hell no, Zorn.
- That's the spirit.

11:33.516 --> 11:36.049
But there is a time and a place,
and I really need a ride.

11:36.085 --> 11:39.653
<i>Has Alan seemed weird to you?
I feel like the clueless mom</i>

11:39.688 --> 11:42.523
- in an afterschool special.
- What, like he's on drugs?

11:42.558 --> 11:44.825
Edie, come on.
Let's be honest with ourselves.

11:44.860 --> 11:47.794
Alangulon's not cool enough
for anyone to offer him drugs.

11:47.830 --> 11:50.063
<i>No, I saw a thing on 60 Minutes</i>

11:50.099 --> 11:52.132
that said even lame kids
can get drugs now.

11:52.167 --> 11:55.802
<i>- Edie, I got to go.
- Linda.</i>

11:55.838 --> 11:58.405
Have you moved your desk
to work among your lessers?

11:58.440 --> 12:00.707
You truly you are
a man of the people!

12:00.743 --> 12:02.376
Zorn, I got demoted.

12:02.411 --> 12:05.156
Save your sucking up
for your new boss, Todd.

12:05.161 --> 12:07.214
What?
But you're the best boss ever.

12:07.249 --> 12:09.016
How could this happen?

12:09.051 --> 12:11.452
Seriously, I don't understand
corporate employment

12:11.453 --> 12:13.854
structure, so I'm
genuinely confused here.

12:13.889 --> 12:15.522
I was already on thin ice
with Erickson,

12:15.558 --> 12:17.157
and then Todd swooped in
and said all the right things

12:17.192 --> 12:19.793
and used all the right...
tennis metaphors.

12:19.828 --> 12:21.595
Well, I mean, you know,
look at the bright side.

12:21.630 --> 12:23.564
Now you can sit out here
in cubicles with all of us

12:23.599 --> 12:26.900
and make Linda jokes.
Screw Linda, right, sir?

12:26.936 --> 12:28.702
You don't need
to call me "sir."

12:28.737 --> 12:30.604
I'm not your superior anymore.

12:30.639 --> 12:32.606
Not my superior?
Huh.

12:32.641 --> 12:34.408
Yeah. W-Wait a second...

12:34.443 --> 12:35.842
not my superior...

12:35.878 --> 12:37.477
dresses...

12:37.513 --> 12:39.646
earrings...

12:39.682 --> 12:43.083
seeing a gynecologist
for your penis... I...

12:43.118 --> 12:46.119
Oh, my God.

12:46.155 --> 12:49.998
You're a woman!

12:50.225 --> 12:51.525
Please, okay? I just...

12:51.560 --> 12:53.527
I need more Zephyritol.
I'm desperate.

12:53.562 --> 12:56.463
Well... there is an old saying
in the medical community:

12:56.498 --> 12:58.231
the first taste is free.

12:58.267 --> 13:00.500
After that, bitch better
have my money.

13:00.536 --> 13:02.903
- $500 to be exact.
- What?

13:02.938 --> 13:05.339
No. Come on.
I need those pills.

13:05.374 --> 13:08.408
I didn't just change my legs,
it changed my entire life.

13:08.444 --> 13:10.577
I finally felt like the Alan
that I've always wanted to be.

13:10.613 --> 13:13.046
You know? Okay, the Alan that
can just walk up to anybody

13:13.082 --> 13:16.316
and say, "Inspect me.
You'll find nothing weird."

13:16.352 --> 13:18.986
- Just have a heart.
- I'm West Zephyrian.

13:19.021 --> 13:21.788
I actually don't have a heart.
There is a ghost in my chest

13:21.824 --> 13:23.924
that scares the blood
around my body.

13:23.959 --> 13:26.259
So give me the money,
or get ready

13:26.295 --> 13:28.662
for some serious
withdrawal symptoms.

13:28.697 --> 13:29.896
Withdrawal?

13:41.494 --> 13:42.726
This site says
I should confront Alan

13:42.762 --> 13:44.461
and demand he tell me
what's going on.

13:44.497 --> 13:47.565
And if he refuses...
I should...

13:47.600 --> 13:50.701
send him to Bible
reeducation camp.

13:50.736 --> 13:52.102
What do you think, Craig?

13:52.138 --> 13:55.039
- Craig!
- I'm sorry. It's just the sandman

